modules.description: Implements WebSocket server logic using Mirage flow-based sockets. Handles incoming connections by creating a WebSocket handshake and managing message input with provided handler functions. Designed for building MirageOS-based network services that require bidirectional communication over WebSocket.

This module implements a WebSocket client that connects to a remote server using a provided network flow. It handles the WebSocket handshake, upgrades the connection, and dispatches incoming messages to user-defined handlers. It works with network flows, WebSocket configurations, and input handlers to manage bidirectional communication over WebSockets. Use this to build clients that interact with WebSocket-based APIs, such as real-time messaging services or live data feeds.

Implements WebSocket server and client logic using Mirage flow-based sockets. The server module handles incoming connections with WebSocket handshakes and message routing, while the client module connects to remote servers, upgrades connections, and dispatches messages. Use these modules to build MirageOS network services with bidirectional communication, such as real-time messaging or live data streaming applications.
